meta_description: 59 percent of Israelis aged 60-69 have already received a third Pfizer shot following a spike in serious cases due to the delta variant, and it’s reducing the rate of transmission

article_title: What full FDA approval of Pfizer could mean for vaccination rates
meta_description: With the Pfizer/BioNTech vaccine expected to be given full approval by the US Food and Drug Administration in the coming days, health experts say the decision may drive more Americans toward receiving Covid-19 vaccines.

article_title: Breakthrough COVID-19 cases are becoming more common. Here's what you need to know.
meta_description: COVID-19 vaccines were never promised to be 100% effective, and experts are united in saying they remain the best way to combat the pandemic.

article_title: COVID in Israel: 645 Patients in Serious Condition, 7,761 New Cases
meta_description: Thousands received the third jab over the weekend as the eligibility age was lowered to 40 and up; so far 1.3 million Israelis received the third dose of the vaccine

article_title: Opinion: Booster shots alone will not save us
meta_description: Given this current landscape, a booster makes a lot of sense. What we must not do, however, is assume the third shot is the charm, writes Dr. Kent Sepkowitz. Rather, the booster is another temporary measure that will provide months of less worry.

article_title: Though young and healthy, unvaccinated father dies of COVID
meta_description: Healthy and in their 30s, Christina and Josh Tidmore figured they were low-risk for COVID-19.  With conflicting viewpoints about whether to get vaccinated against the virus filling their social media feeds and social circles, they decided to wait.  On July 20, Josh came home from work with a slight cough initially thought to be sinus trouble.

article_title: Alabama doctor Jason Valentine refuses to treat patients not vaccinated for COVID-19
meta_description: ‘I cannot continue to watch my patients suffer and die from an eminently preventable disease.’

article_title: Before dying of COVID-19, mom of four pleads: 'I need my kids to get vaccinated'
meta_description: Lydia and Lawrence Rodriguez were both unvaccinated when they tested positive for COVID-19 after returning from a church camp. Both later died.
